abstract = {In the agricultural sector, farmers often face persistent issues such as delayed payments, opaque transaction processes, and over-reliance on intermediaries. This paper presents a blockchain-based paddy crop marketplace aimed at establishing direct trust between farmers and buyers using Ethereum smart contracts. The system employs an escrow-based payment model, where funds are securely locked onchain until the buyer confirms delivery. A mobile-first platform, developed with React Native and supported by a Node.js backend and PostgreSQL database, enables role-specific access for both buyers and farmers. Payment-critical actions are automated and traceable through smart contracts deployed via the Hardhat development framework, ensuring transparency and transactional integrity. The hybrid design leverages blockchain for secure payment handling while maintaining crop listings and general transaction metadata off-chain, secured by backend validations. Although the prototype operates in a simulated Ethereum environment, it demonstrates the feasibility of a localized, mobile-first, wallet-free solution tailored for paddy farmers in Karnataka, India. The system minimises manual intervention, promotes fair and transparent transactions, and lays the groundwork for future scalability, integration with widely used payment systems, and extended dispute resolution mechanisms.},
